[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "In the land which the Lord sware unto your fathers to give them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—“It is not written here ‘to give ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "you,’ ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but ‘to give ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "them.’ Hence we find the resurrection of the dead taught in the Law.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If this were the remark of a Christian commentator, it would be thought fanciful; but it is only the comment of a Jew. And ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Jewish belief in the literal fulfilment of these promises to Abraham and Isaac and Jacob, simply on the ground of God’s word, is an unquestionable fact, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "whatever may be thought of it. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which is singularly pointed. God “gave him (Abraham) none inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on; yet ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He promised that He would give it to him for a possession, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and to his seed after him,” besides.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 11:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 11:21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "As the days of heaven — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As long as the heaven keeps its place, and continues its influences upon the earth. Thus the psalmist says of the son of David, the Messiah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His seed shall endure for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
